radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis; diffuse hypoattenuation of the liver consistent with mild hepatic steatosis; hyperemic, enlarged appendix measuring up to 12 mm with surrounding fat stranding; 4 mm appendicolith at the appendix base; no pleural effusions, focal lesions, intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation, free air, free fluid, adjacent fluid collections, or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
